* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution calculates \(P(X > Y)\) by finding the distribution of \(X - Y\), which is normal with mean \(-1\) and variance \(25\). Standardizing gives \(P(X - Y > 0) = P(Z > 0.2)\), where \(Z\) is standard normal. Using the standard normal table, \(P(Z < 0.2) \approx 0.5793\), so \(P(Z > 0.2) = 1 - 0.5793 = 0.4207\), rounded to three decimal places as \(0.421\).

The final answer is \(0.421\), and no unit is specified for the probability.

