* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution evaluates the integral \(\int_0^{0.4} \frac{\Gamma(7)}{\Gamma(4) \Gamma(3)} y^3(1-y)^2  dy\) by first simplifying the constant factor to 60, expanding the integrand to \(y^3 - 2y^4 + y^5\), and finding the antiderivative. After evaluating the antiderivative from 0 to 0.4 and multiplying by 60, the result is 0.1792. This value is exact and has no units.

The final answer is $0.1792$.
